dc_description_s: This line shapefile represents streets and roads in Baghdad, Iraq. This dataset includes attributes such as street length and MPH/KMH speeds, as well as routing information such as elevation, tunnels, ramps, and bridges. This layer is part of a collection of 2010 routing data for Baghdad. This dataset is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. LeadDog Consulting. (2010). Streets and Roads, Baghdad, 2010. LeadDog Consulting. Available at: http://purl.stanford.edu/jp541cf7974.
